records.addlTxt: Wisconsin Community Service compliance letter received and filed.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing. Defendant to have no contact with victim A (or their residence)/witness A (or their residence) listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney. Defendant to comply with GPS monitoring through Wisconsin Community Services.  Defendant is not to come within 0.5 mile of Victim A, listed in the Victim Identification Key, or their residence, employment, school or anywhere they frequent. The Defendant to report to WCS within one (1) business day of being released. Defendant allowed one trip to the residence accompanied by a peace/police officer to obtain personal items. Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons/firearms.

1:50 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marrufo. Defendant Kenneth J Ringer in court, in custody. 

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. 
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. 
Court advises of right to an attorney. 
NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT. 
The Court puts the Defendant on notice that if it receives a WCS non-compliance letter, that the Court will forfeit bail and issue a warrant.
Hearing scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 11:00 am.
To Seal Victim/Witness Identification Key, Signed by Judge Jennifer R. Dorow on October 11th, 2022.
